    <string name="help_tutorial_0_header">Add Reminder</string>
    <string name="help_tutorial_0">To add a new reminder press the + action button on the main page</string>

    <string name="help_tutorial_1_header">Title &amp; Content</string>
    <string name="help_tutorial_1">The reminder title will show on the main page and on the top of notifications.
        The content will show in the body of the notification and on the reminder summary page.</string>

    <string name="help_tutorial_2_header">Timing Specific</string>
    <string name="help_tutorial_2">Choose Specific for a single reminder at a certain time in the day.
    Touch the time shown to pick the reminder time.</string>

    <string name="help_tutorial_3_header">Timing Range</string>
    <string name="help_tutorial_3">Choose Range for one or more reminders throughout the day.
    Touch the start and end times to set the range.
    Next choose how many reminders you want during those times.
    Finally choose if you want the times randomized or at an even interval.</string>

    <string name="help_tutorial_4_header">Repeat</string>
    <string name="help_tutorial_4">Highlight the days of the week where you want to be reminded</string>

    <string name="help_tutorial_5_header">Notification</string>
    <string name="help_tutorial_5">Customize the notification with a custom tone, vibrate, priority, and LED color.
        High priority may only work if either or both vibrate and a tone are enabled (depending on device).</string>

    <string name="help_tutorial_6_header">Reminder Summary</string>
    <string name="help_tutorial_6">The number of notifications shown and clicked are logged and shown on the summary page.
    The statistics are available on a per day basis for the last 30 days along with a lifetime total.</string>

    <string name="help_tutorial_7_header">The Notification</string>
    <string name="help_tutorial_7">For reminders that require action you can use notification buttons Acknowledge and Dismiss.
    Swiping away the reminder counts as a dismiss and clicking it counts as Acknowledging it.
    Using the notification action buttons will not open the app. By default clicking the notification opens the app. Change this in settings if you want a different behavior.</string>

